item.title: WA down to three active coronavirus cases
item.description: Just three active coronavirus cases remain in Western Australia, where people are returning to offices and cafes under eased restrictions.

item.title: Overseas students waiting on Vic support
item.description: International students in Victoria are still waiting to receive support payments promised by the state government almost a month ago.

item.title: No NSW bail for alleged Qld parent killer
item.description: A Queensland man will remain behind bars in NSW for at least another day before potentially being extradited to the Sunshine State over his parents' murder.

item.title: Canadian air force jet crash kills one
item.description: A jet from the Canadian air force's Snowbirds aerobatics team that was on a tour to lift spirits during the coronavirus outbreak has crashed in British Columbia, killing a crew member and injuring another, defence officials say.

item.title: Fisherman washed overboard off Qld
item.description: Authorities are searching for a fisherman washed overboard from a trawler in rough seas off Queensland's Sunshine Coast.

item.title: PM urges teamwork as workplaces move home
item.description: Nearly half of all Australians with jobs are working from home in a massive change to workplace structure forced by the coronavirus crisis.

item.title: Light plane crashes in regional Victoria
item.description: A light plane pilot has survived a crash in regional Victoria with minor injuries.

item.title: Morrison has low-key election anniversary
item.description: Scott Morrison has marked a year since his miraculous election victory with a low-key celebratory email to supporters.

item.title: Latest snapshot of the coronavirus impact
We may never beat virus: Qld’s top doctor
item.description: Queensland's chief health officer has thrown her support behind the decision to keep the state's borders closed, saying coronavirus may never be eradicated.
